HEADWORD: Fenowed
<hw>Fen"owed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>fynig</ets>
musty, <ets>fynegean</ets> to become musty or filthy: cf.
<ets>fennig</ets> fenny, muddy, dirty, fr. <ets>fen</ets> fen. Cf.
<er>Finew</er>.]</ety> <def>Corrupted; decayed; moldy. See
<er>Vinnewed</er>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Dr.
Favour.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

